        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued April 2 at 1:24AM CDT until April 2 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerous rip currents and minor coastal flooding,
mainly during times of high tides expected.

* WHERE...Gulf-facing beaches, including the Matagorda
Peninsula, Brazoria County beaches, Galveston Island and the
Bolivar Peninsula.

* WHEN...From 5 AM CDT early this morning through this evening.

* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water. Minor flooding of lots, parks, and roads
with only isolated road closures possible.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth.</instruction>
